Package jetbrains.mps.workbench.choose

Interface ElementPresentation<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the element from the list
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LanguagesPresentation, ModelsPresentation, ModulesPresentation, NavigationTargetPresentation, NodesPresentation
    public interface ElementPresentation<T>
    This is what chooser model needs to know about list elements to represent them in the UI.

    • Method Detail

      • names

        void names​(@NotNull
           Iterable<T> elements,
           @NotNull
           BiConsumer<T,​String> nameConsumer)
        Batch operation to get names of multiple elements. Comes handy when e.g. a lock is needed to process elements, and render(Object, ElementDescriptor) per element operation} may be ineffective/excessive. This method is invoked from the same thread as ChooseByNameModel.getNames(boolean), which I assume to be EDT/UI (though hard to prove). However, since it's possible the method to get invoked from another thread, it's unreasonable to expect EDT/UI thread (nor there's any need to, provided method is focused on names)
        Parameters:
        elements - chooser items of interest
        nameConsumer - sink for element-name pairs, (not necessarily supports multi-thread use)

      • canRender

        boolean canRender​(@Nullable
                  Object element)
        Mostly shall tell if object is an instance of <T>
        Parameters:
        element - chooser list item, most likely (though not necessarily) is one of elements we pick from, but also may be some auxiliary (e.g. category string) element. Denoted as Nullable not because I've seen it null, just as I have no guarantee whatsoever from underlying popup, and don't have enough time to investigate now.
        Returns:
        true if render(Object, ElementDescriptor) call is feasible

      • render

        void render​(@NotNull
            T element,
            @NotNull
            ElementDescriptor presentation)
        Populate descriptor with relevant UI data. Fields are initialized with default values as appropriate for the list renderer (e.g. null or empty string), clients shall not update fields that they know nothing about. This method is invoked from EDT/UI thread.
